Punished for her alleged links to witchcraft, a Shannon Road informal settlement resident, 27, bore the brunt of the community’s scathing wrath when she was assaulted, doused with petrol and set alight, on Wednesday night. The victim was rushed to hospital with serious injuries. Captain Nqobile Gwala, police spokesperson said: “We can confirm the incident that took place on 11 November at 7pm at Shannon Drive informal settlement in Sydenham.
The a 27-year-old victim was allegedly assaulted and burnt with petrol by members of the community. “She ran into the bushes where she was found by the police with serious injuries. She was taken to hospital for medical attention. The victim was accused by the community of being involved in witchcraft.” There were no reported arrests and investigations are ongoing.